  "texts": [
    "The crack detection task is a significant class imbalance problem, i.e., many more undamaged regions than damaged regions in each sample.",
    "Precision and recall are inappropriate metrics if we consider only damaged and undamaged classes since the model can trivially achieve high performance when most (or all) pixels are labelled as undamaged.",
    "In this case, we must use them to quantify a model's performance.",
    "The harmonic mean of precision and recall (Eq. 13) is called the F-1 score, which is equivalent to the Dice coefficient (DSC).",
    "Besides DSC, Intersection over Union (IoU) metric is another commonly used metric for semantic segmentation tasks."
  ],
